programme.desc: Kevin Dykstra and his team learn that their search for a fortune in gold at the bottom of Lake Michigan may be connected to the assassination of President Abraham Lincoln.

programme.title: The Tesla Files S1E1
programme.desc: Researcher Marc Seifer recruits astrophysicist Travis Taylor and journalist Jason Stapleton to help unravel the mystery of inventor Nikola Tesla's missing files, confiscated by the US.

programme.title: Programmed To Kill: Melioidosis -殺人程式: 類鼻疽
programme.desc: This is the story of Melioidosis, a life-threatening tropical disease in Southeast Asia and Australia which can remain dormant in a victim for weeks, months, even decades, or just kill within 48 hours.

programme.title: Swamp People S10E3
programme.desc: Joey and Zak need a bird's-eye view to find the beast breaking all their lines. Ronnie and Ashley pursue gators on land. Jacob and Dusty try their luck hunting giant beasts in a small boat.

programme.title: Swamp People S10E4
programme.desc: Joey and Zak use an off-road buggy to chase a giant bull gator. Daniel and Big Tee reach a honey hole, while Willie has an old score to settle in the eerie Black Lagoon.

programme.title: Mountain Men S8E106
programme.desc: Eustace and Raleigh battle a polar vortex to get their lumber business back online, Mike braves a bear-infested landscape in search of fresh meat, and Morgan and Margaret chase the migrating caribou.

programme.title: Swamp Mysteries With Troy Landry S1E2
programme.desc: When the ocean's deadliest creature invades the Louisiana swamps, Troy answers the call.

programme.title: Alone S6E2
programme.desc: As they close in on the one week mark, the survivalists make some risky choices in order to eat. Serious infection becomes a very real possibility, driving one participant to consider pulling out early.

programme.title: The Pickers S12E17
programme.sub-title: Best Of: Best Of The West
programme.desc: Mike and Frank head West to where the buffalo roam and the skies are not cloudy all day in search of the most perfect picks on the range.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E5
programme.desc: After abandoning his former home due to lack of resources, hunter-gatherer Matt journeys to the lower elevation canyons of southern Utah to find a new area to call home. He's hopeful this land will have the necessary resources he needs to survive the cold months. Winter has finally come, so Matt must work quickly to build a permanent shelter and protect himself from the elements.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E1
programme.desc: Car lover Chris has had his beloved, Ferrari engined, 1971 Fiat Dino coupe for nearly 25 years. The former engine mechanic had to put the restoration on hold when he was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer. Now it's up to Tim and Fuzz to get this rusting Dino back to its best. Tim takes a drive in one of the most beautiful cars in the world and Fuzz gets his hands on a Ferrari racing engine for the very first time.

programme.title: Maneater Manhunt E3
programme.desc: As their habitat shrinks and their wild prey declines, the tigers of Chitwan National Park in Nepal attack people more frequently. Gordon travels to Nepal to look into the increasing reports of man-eating tigers and investigates one particular tigress named Nangara Pothi, meaning the claw, who has killed at least ten people since 2008, unlocking the myths and mysteries of the serial man-eater.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E6
programme.sub-title: Dave Bautista In Glen Canyon, Arizona
programme.desc: Bear Grylls takes former WWE world champion and action star Dave Bautista on a super-sized adventure in the Arizona desert. Navigating through perilous canyon descents, brutal falls and the raging Colorado River will be no easy task. With Bear as his tag team partner, Dave is up for the challenge to see if he still has that fight inside - but Mother Nature could prove to be his toughest opponent yet in this match of a lifetime!

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E9
programme.desc: Ralph and Ranen are tasked with fulfilling Afzal Kahn's dream of producing one of the fastest road cars in the world. Kahn challenges them to engineer a car to beat his Bugatti Veyron in a straight quarter mile race. Their answer is a Nissan GTR with a specialist Japanese ECU hack. In three weeks they must overhaul the GTR and take it to Santa Pod Raceway for a supercar showdown.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E7
programme.desc: Welcome to Tokyo, Greer! After meeting up with her travel guide Keiichi in the middle of the famous Shibuya intersection, Greer kicks off her 48 hours in Japan. Their adventures take them to a Ninja Restaurant, on a helicopter flight above Tokyo and so much more.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E8
programme.desc: This time, Greer delves a little deeper into a city on home turf: Darwin! Her guide is travel consultant Itimai, who has a show-stopping 48 hours lined up, including stunning Top End scenery, unique fusion cuisine and yes, catching sight of a crocodile – watch out Greer!

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E1
programme.desc: Its Bluefin Season in the Outer Banks of North Carolina, and New England's best fisherman have followed the migration down to catch a piece of the action. But, an all-time low season quota means finding Southern hospitality won't be easy. Northern and Southern fisherman fight to get the first catch and mother nature isn't taking sides.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E3
programme.desc: MIA CBP searches and questions a passenger coming from Jamaica because of his suspicious story and new suitcase. After finding anomalies in the bag, they begin to suspect he might be smuggling narcotics. JFK CBP Officers find a suspicious package containing cowboy boots and suspect something is hidden inside. At JFK, HSI opens pistons filled with cocaine, which leads to a controlled delivery and raid of the home to which the package was addressed.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E1
programme.desc: Car lover Chris has had his beloved, Ferrari engined, 1971 Fiat Dino coupe for nearly 25 years. The former engine mechanic had to put the restoration on hold when he was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer. Now it's up to Tim and Fuzz to get this rusting Dino back to its best. Tim takes a drive in one of the most beautiful cars in the world and Fuzz gets his hands on a Ferrari racing engine for the very first time.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E2
programme.desc: China is the world's longest continuous civilization, but as the nation modernizes, there's a new thirst to rediscover its roots. Historian Sam Willis investigates the importance of the family to Chinese civilization and how it became the building block of Chinese society, shaping the nation from past to present.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E1
programme.desc: Actor Ted Danson and special guests The Blue Man Group play along with host Keegan-Michael Key as we learn how our brains distinguish fact from fiction. Games include identifying real vs. fake news headlines, spotting a poker face out of a group of World Series Poker Champions and figuring out which photo conveys the truth. In addition, master mentalist Lior Suchard predicts who's lying when it comes to hiding a treasured object, and Danson takes a ride through the show's mental obstacle course, known as the Gauntlet.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E9
programme.desc: Greer discovers the best Hong Kong city has to offer with the help of Alan, a local travel consultant. Their adventures include visiting the incredible Big Budda on Lantau Island, enjoying mouth-watering dim sum, early morning Tai Chi and so much more!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E10
programme.desc: Greer sees LA from a whole new angle, thanks to local guide and travel consultant Kelly. We're talking rooftop bars, a rooftop cinema, skyline dining and she even gets in the water to learn to surf at Venice Beach. It's a full 48 hours in LA and, for Greer and Kelly, this is just the tip of the iceberg...

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E10
programme.desc: Afzal Kahn has been contacted by a client asking him to produce a vehicle capable of surviving winter conditions, taking on difficult terrain and crossing deep snow. Ralph and Ranen modify an Audi A8 to withstand -40C, fit bespoke tracks to the four corners of the vehicle and a snow plough. To make sure this vehicle stands out from the crowd even more, Afzal Kahn gives the car a complete overhaul.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E2
programme.desc: Petrol head Tony's Jaguar Mk2 has been in his family for over 40 years. Due to complications following a stomach operations he's not been able to restore the car himself and it's sat neglected in the garage for nearly two decades. With Fuzz battling to start the Jags engine and Tim having to get his hand dirty making parts it will be a race against time to get this British classic finished on time.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E3
programme.desc: The rise of modern lifestyles in China has led to the explosion of the health and fitness industry, but this is far from new. Historian Sam Willis is on a journey to explore the health practices of the ancient Chinese. From the way they understood the body and its workings, to different traditions that developed to cure disease, Sam discovers how age-old concepts still loom large in the nation today.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E2
programme.desc: JFK CBP question an elderly woman arriving from Peru. They suspect narcotics are cleverly concealed in bottles that she's carrying. At MIA, HSI carries out a daring sting, delivering cocaine that was hidden in a shipment of paintings. And at LAX, a set of unclaimed suitcases arouses suspicions. Officers believe the bags may contain contraband.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E10
programme.desc: Two atoms from different parts of the universe meet on a small planet. How a deadly embrace between science and state altered the fate of the world, and a gripping cautionary tale of others who grew used to living in the shadow of grave danger until it killed them all except one.

programme.title: Is It Real? (30 Mins) E17
programme.desc: Dan Brown's controversial book, “The Da Vinci's Code,” has raised huge controversy because it had made at least a couple of damaging claims that the author insist to be fact. The documentary seeks to uncover the truth behind these claims, including claims of whether Mary Magdalene may have been the wife of Jesus, and interviews with Father William Stetson and various authors of books.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E7
programme.sub-title: Joel Mchale In Arizona Slot Canyons
programme.desc: The often clever, always snarky actor and comedian Joel McHale joins Bear Grylls in the Arizona desert for an adventure unlike any other. They set out to traverse a massive slot canyon in hopes of surviving the wild, but first they have to survive one another! Huge cliffs, nasty food, and unorthodox survival strategies abound in this hilarious misadventure!

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E3
programme.desc: Engineer Chad Zdenek joins a salvage team to tear apart the world's biggest hovercraft and reveal the engineering innovations that made it a legend of its time. In San Diego, he takes controls of the US Navy hovercraft fighting wars and saving lives around the world.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E7
programme.desc: Jordan is headed to St. Louis. Known as the gateway to the west, this city is a gateway to a wide variety of culinary delights. Jordan kicks off his journey at a restaurant close to his own heart. Guerilla Street Foods serves up Filipino cuisine with a mid-west riff. Pork served street style with calamansi sauce and a poached egg, and fried chicken that finds the perfect blend of sweet, salty and tangy.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E8
programme.desc: Jordan's journey takes a turn full south with a trip to Music City. While Nashville may be best known for its music, it's next known for its mouthwatering cuisine. Jordan starts off his journey through this southern jewel at the Butcher and Bee, where globally inspired share plates bring joy to customers at all hours of the night.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E2
programme.desc: The best fisherman on the Eastern Seaboard continue their battle for bluefin in the Outer Banks of North Carolina. Last season's champion maintains his lead over both the Northern and Southern fleets. But with captains on both sides hungry for paychecks, a rapidly evaporating fish quota and an angry ocean, can the fisherman outwit the fish?

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E10
programme.desc: Taking off during a major storm, a brand-new 737 falls from the sky over West Africa, and an international group of investigators soon descends on Cameroon. Submerged in mud and water, Kenya Airlines Flight 507 crashed into a mangrove swamp, killing everyone on board. And while investigators ultimately pinpoint one fatal mistake that triggered the tragedy, they also uncover a lethal cascade of issues that sent the passenger jet spiralling toward the ground.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E7
programme.sub-title: The Search For Intelligent Life On Earth
programme.desc: A revelation of the hidden underground network that is a collaboration of four kingdoms of life, and a true first contact story between humans and beings who communicate in a symbolic language and have maintained a representative democracy for many tens of millions of years.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E8
programme.desc: The mysterious untold story of the scientist who figured out how to go the Moon while fighting for his life in a WWI trench. He wrote a letter to fifty years in the future. It made the Apollo Mission possible. And the saga of the twenty-year long odyssey of a robotic explorer ordered to commit suicide on another world.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E2
programme.desc: Actress Tiffany Haddish and director Jordan Peele join Keegan-Michael Key to play games that show how Hollywood pros manipulate our brains to make us feel genuine emotion while watching movies. Challenges and demos include taking a closer look at some of the bizarre tactics used to create sound effects in movies, spotting the stuntman, identifying a performer in disguise and illuminating how filmmakers manipulate our brains with editing. Sound designer Craig Pennigan shows us how sound alters the way our brains perceive a scene, Haddish tests her mental strength and agility in the Gauntlet, and mentalist Lior Suchard stuns the crowd with an amazing mind-reading trick.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E9
programme.desc: Jordan's southern tour continues in the jewel of the south – Charleston, South Carolina. He starts off his trip at one of the city's finest taprooms, Craftmen Taphouse where each menu items is expertly crafted to pair with one of the many beers. Jordan tucks into crowd pleasing Mexican style street fare with a zesty scallop ceviche and roasted street corn.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E10
programme.desc: Jordan is in Atlanta where cosmopolitan glamour and southern traditions collide. In this sitting, everyone is vying for a seat at the best tables, and that's even more true late night. Jordan's kicks off his Atlanta adventure at 5 Church, a midtown haven dishing out Chef Scotley's signature southern comfort.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E4
programme.desc: The Brent Delta oil rig extracted oil and gas from beneath one of the roughest seas on the planet for over 40 years. With the oil fields running dry the rig is being taken apart at a purpose-built reinforced quay on the north east coast of Britain.

programme.title: The Happenings E1
programme.desc: Barry and Stuart arrive in the quiet town of Stamford in England. Their aim is to make the residents believe aliens have arrived. To convince the public that extraterrestrials have been watching them for years, they go undercover as filmmakers and paranormal researchers, and plan an alien abduction and work to convince residents that the extraterrestrials brainwashed their animals.

programme.title: Running Wild With Bear Grylls E8
programme.sub-title: Channing Tatum In The Mountains Of Norway
programme.desc: It's been five years since Channing Tatum first appeared on Running Wild, and he's back for more- this time in the wilds of Norway! Their journey kicks off by skydiving into brutal terrain where giant boulder fields and towering cliffs stand in the way of extraction. During their seven-mile trek, Bear tests Channing to see how far he's come as a survivor - from foraging for food to Navy SEAL style cold-water emersion training. Channing even learns the ancient art of trout tickling!

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E9
programme.desc: What makes a car worth a million Euros? The answer for Horacio Pagani is a supercar that perfectly blends art and engineering, that has unsurpassed power, performance and luxury, the finest possible raw materials and in which every single one of its 4700 components will be recognized as a work of art. This film tells the story of Pagani's successor to his world famous Zonda.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E4
programme.desc: In order to feed passengers 35,000 feet up in the air, there's an army of chefs on the ground in the mega flight kitchens of TajSATS Delhi dishing up over 22,000 meals a day - from Economy to First Class!

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E3
programme.desc: As a herd of massive fish hit the waters of North Carolina, the competition heats up between the Northern and Southern fleets. The curse of the Outer Banks strikes again for one of New England's best fisherman. And with the small quota driving up prices, one Northerner takes a gamble to try and nab a monster blue fin, while the smallest boat in the fleet struggles to land their biggest-ever catch.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E5
programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Manuel Noriega to rise from poverty to become dictator of Panama for six tumultuous years in the 1980s. As Chief of Intelligence he was the most feared man in Panama. He developed connections inside and outside the country that made him rich, powerful, and a key ally of the US in the region, while also working for Fidel Castro and the Medellin drug cartel, among others.

programme.title: 100%: Planes
programme.desc: 100% Planes tells amazing aviation stories from around the world, featuring aircrafts from the smallest microlight to the biggest cargo plane, and everything in between. Circumnavigate the globe, travel to the most beautiful and exotic locations, and hear the stories of pilots flying the most interesting and unusual planes.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E1
programme.desc: Morgan Freeman delves into why many religious believers desire to see God in human form - and how that strengthens their faith. From a living Kumari Goddess in the mountains of Nepal, to the Crown of Thorns many Christians believe was worn by Jesus during the crucifixion, Morgan will discover that these tangible connections help people make sense of the divine.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E3
programme.desc: Actor Anthony Anderson and his younger 'Black-ish' co-star Marsai Martin face off in a series of games with Keegan-Michael Key to explore the surprising differences between adults' and kids' brains. Challenges involve language, reflexes and reaction times, and risk-taking and mind control - all before the two co-stars face off in the Gauntlet's mental obstacle course. Plus, field correspondent Cara Santa Maria pits the driving skills of teens against those of adults by reversing the controls of a go-cart, using neuroscience to explain why one group performs much better than the other.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E5
programme.desc: What does it take to prepare over 10,000 meals a day for discerning clients of the Indian Railways and more? IRCTC shows you how it's done inside one of its central mega kitchens.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E7
programme.desc: The latest versions of the original pony car are built in Ford's Mustang Factory. Amazingly, both the cars and the factory are designed to produce 4 different models, from the base V6 to a 650HP fire breathing V8. In terms of horsepower, the 650HP V8 is the most powerful V8 built anywhere in the world.

programme.title: Notre Dame: Race Against The Inferno
programme.desc: On 15th April 2019, during Holy Monday Mass, the world's most famous cathedral caught fire. Notre-Dame de Paris was ablaze in minutes, as an epic battle unfolded for heroic French firefighters. Under the gaze of the world's media, they fought the inferno for more than 15 hours. Exclusive footage and interviews bring vividly to life the moment-by-moment courage of the Paris fire and police services, as they put their lives on the line to save this historic building.

programme.title: The Story Of God With Morgan Freeman S3E2
programme.desc: Morgan Freeman explores the role that the devil plays in various religions. From the ascetic monks in the Judean desert to the Buddhists of Nepal, he'll learn what purpose the figure of the devil serves. Is the devil a force of evil in the world that needs to be conquered? Or is it something that each one of us needs to conquer in our own heart?

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E6
programme.desc: A look at the techniques used by Idi Amin to rise from humble beginnings and build a powerful dictatorship in Uganda. Amin became an expert at deploying military force to achieve political power, a lesson he first learned from the British as a soldier in the colonial army. Through a combination of populist charm and brutal violence, backed up by a vast police state, Idi Amin managed to rule Uganda for eight years.

programme.title: Confucius Was A Foodie S3E1
programme.desc: This episode sees Christine learning firsthand the very challenging ‘how to' of harvesting sea salt in Thailand's dramatically beautiful salt fields. Cushing visits the area's most unusual market that is regularly disrupted by the Maeklong Railway going right through it's center!

programme.title: Food Lab S2E61
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys stop at Honey Tasmania on the main street of Exeter. Rebecca informs Ben about the importance of bee's and the Tasmanian rainforests. programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E5
programme.desc: The palaces, cathedrals and museums of St. Petersburg represent some of the finest architecture on Earth. The city was built as the shining symbol of the Russian empire's golden age. Now a select few must safeguard these cherished relics of the past to reveal the city's splendor once again.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E9
programme.desc: In the 24 hour build special George Clarke takes on the 600 year old legend of the Ty Unnos; a piece of Welsh folklore that claims that if you can build a house with four walls, a roof and have a fire burning in your hearth in less than a day, then that house and the ground beneath it is yours.

programme.title: World's Biggest Festival: Kumbh Mela
programme.desc: Film maker Diego Bunuel immerses himself in Indian culture by attending the Kumbh Mela, the world's largest religious festival that happens every 12 years. He meets sadhus who express their extreme devotion by pulling a car with penis, standing constantly for 10 years, raising an arm for 40 years and being buried alive for days! Join Diego to experience this dazzling spectacle of spiritual fervor!

A soothing journey that finds ultra luxurious healing centers such as Como Shambhala amidst the lush jungles of Ubud - to a hands on cooking stint at the Balinese fusion restaurant Mozaic, to checking out true African style Safaris in the heart of Bali. Helicopter rides over volcanos and reef-rescuing innovative dive resorts. This is an adventure true to the Island Hunter style.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E1
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent. It's a journey of a lifetime for the unlikely duo as they traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Meeting with local historian Chen Ban, they trace the footsteps of Hakka pioneers along a series of mountain trails that formed the backbone of their livelihood, transporting commodities and goods. Travelling further south, they get their hands dirty and learn how camphor, one of Taiwan's treasures is traditionally extracted. The duo also learn more about a tea that was created by the Hakka, that embodies the very spirit of what it means to be part of a ethnicity that were once outcasts.

programme.desc: Mokukchung is the cultural capital for the Ao Nagas. Aos is one of the major Naga tribes of Nagaland. As Pablo visits Mokokchung, he gets to witness the diversity of Nagas at the Moatsumung Festival. A colorful, spirited festival that brings together the entire Naga Community.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E1
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford joins Joe and Laura on ‘Big Blue' a 44ft Sailing Catamaran. Along the way he will jet boat up a river to a remote village, dive with huge bull sharks and track down local chef Lance Seeto to unlock an ancient local recipe.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E2
programme.desc: Fish of the Day host Clarke Gayford shows off his hometown of Gisborne. This includes hand feeding friendly wild stingrays and venturing out to his favourite fishing and diving spots trying to track down an unusual fish called a Pink Maomao. Along the way they encounter huge schools of Kingfish and a couple of friendly sharks.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E65
programme.desc: In the final episode Ben heads back down to his local, the Mersey Bluff Beach, here he creates a simple dish, using some wood roasted salmon. He checks out the Huon Salmon hatchery and has a chat with David Mitchell about their processes. At The University of Queensland Ben is joined by Professor Neena Mitter, who is aiming to change the game of growing avocados, together they make an avocado chutney full of flavour.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E1
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, meets a small community of the Dong tribe, one of China's 55 ethnic minority groups and participates in their unusual celebration of the mid-autumn festival, a ritual marking the last harvest of the year.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E2
programme.desc: Deep in Morocco's Middle Atlas Mountains, Chef Ramsay embarks on an epic adventure to unlock the secrets of the Berber cuisine.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E3
programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett sets sail for the islands of Fiji, where he comes face to face with bull sharks, partakes in ancient Fijian fire walking rituals, and anchors in the remote Lau Islands, a beautiful place with a violent past.

programme.title: Ugly House To Lovely House With George Clarke S2E1
programme.desc: In stunning rural Gloucestershire Simon and Lisa recently bought a carbuncle on the landscape. Originally built in the Dutch barn style this shoddy building was such a nightmare that neighbours compared it to the house in Amityville Horror. Simon hated it so much that he wanted to bulldoze it and start again. George teams the couple up with creative architect Laura Clark. Her challenge is to come up with a scheme to turn this terrifying building into a warm, welcoming, modern home, whilst still retaining some of its character. But with a limited budget and only 9 weeks to play with, Simon and Lisa may have to get their hands dirty if they want to achieve their dream.

programme.title: John Torode's Asia E2
programme.desc: John Torode is in the holy city of Amritsar in the Punjab region of northern India. His first outing takes him to the Golden Temple. What's remarkable about this site besides the temple itself is that it provides free meals to as many as 100,000 people per day, regardless of religion, colour or wealth.

programme.title: San Diego: More To Explore E3
programme.desc: San Diego is known for being on the cutting edge of scientific discovery. Whether that means saving an entire species from near extinction, to pushing the envelope on fine dining and rethinking how we utilize food. Host Robert Reid explores San Diego's smart advancements in technology and the inventive minds behind them.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E2
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent, to explore and understand the relationship of Hakka food and their traditional lifestyle. The unlikely duo traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Along the way, Julian and Natalie meet unique characters and learn that the heart of Hakka cuisine stemmed from their traditional way of living.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E18
programme.desc: Fermentation, Alcohol & beverages: Human migration led to the spread of amazing practices in many parts of the world. People migrated with the treasure of these practices and shared them with other races. Pablo learned more about this diverse country India as he dug through the practices in North East brought by people from countries like Tibet, Burma, Laos, Vietnam.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E3
programme.desc: Clarke travels to Aitutaki and catches up with Bonefish guide Etu, to catch one of the most challenging fish in the World to catch on Fly, the Bonefish. Along the way he catches up with the Prime Minister of the Cook Islands, also a keen fisherman and they head out to track down one of his favourite local fish the Kuta, for local Chef Thomas.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E4
programme.desc: Clarke enjoys a proper adventure off the East Coast of New Zealand taking a boat out to White Island, a very active volcano 50kms offhsore. Here conditions can quickly change. Catching his target fish after plenty of false alarms, Clarke takes it back to chef Josh in the local town of Whakatane. Josh specialises in celiac friendly quisine and his Hapuku dish does not dissapoint.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E1
programme.desc: Jen discovers the incredible treasures of Cambodia including Angkor Wat as well as meeting the most interesting locals.

programme.title: Route Awakening S3E2
programme.desc: Dr Jonathan Clements, historian, author and TV host, continues his exploration of the Dong tribe and visits a village considered the living fossil of ancient traditions where he learns folk crafts from the elderly and witnesses an elaborate Dong style funeral.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E3
programme.desc: Chef Gordon Ramsay travels down the Mekong River in Laos, Southeast Asia on an adventure to unlock the secrets of its cuisine.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E4
programme.desc: Host Ellis Emmett has his first brush with royalty on the island kingdoms of Wallis & Futuna. But it is the life of a lone man, living simply on a remote island, which truly captures Ellis' imagination. Ever the adventurer, Ellis dives into a lake that, according to local legend, is full of mysteries and monsters.

programme.title: Man Vs Shark
programme.desc: Marine biologist and shark suit inventor, Jeremiah Sullivan, attempts to intentionally get bitten by a deadly tiger shark and survive.

programme.title: World's Deadliest Compilations E1
programme.desc: In the animal kingdom, the law is always eat or be eaten. But some sophisticated predators take down prey in brutal and terrifying ways. These are some of nature's worst ways to die, and they are neither quick nor painless.

programme.title: The World's Most Famous Tiger
programme.desc: Known as the Queen of Ranthambore, Machli is the most famous tiger in the world. The legendary tigress is a fearsome warrior known for her daring exploits. And she's the mother of an incredible four litters of cubs. She's survived longer than most tigers in the wild. Threatened by her own offspring, the aging Machli is now in jeopardy of losing her reign of the best territory inside India's Ranthambore National Park.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E1
programme.desc: A shambling hoard of zombies has invaded the airwaves, but they're nothing new. The animal world has been out-doing zombies since the beginning of time. In this episode, we go in search of nature's finest examples of zombie-like behavior.

programme.title: Man Vs Shark
programme.desc: Marine biologist and shark suit inventor, Jeremiah Sullivan, attempts to intentionally get bitten by a deadly tiger shark and survive.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E8
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley participates in a race pitting human runners against reindeer, five muskox undergo pregnancy tests, and Daisy participates in a family reunion.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E4
programme.desc: Mmamotse's rule has turned the Kingdom upside down. Her army run rampant, but her legacy now depends on a Princess stepping up to the throne. As the flood waters retreat, Dikeledi readies her cubs for escape, but must risk crossing enemy territory. And a run in with the Matahta Pride brings things into focus for Pula, as she begins training her young assassin. In the Savage Kingdom, the young hold the key to power - the future is theirs for the taking.

programme.title: 700 Sharks
programme.desc: In Polynesia, the largest school of sharks will be studied at an unprecedented scale. An international team of scientists will dive among the pack of 700 squalls. 3 years of preparation were needed to approach the sharks at night, when they are most aggressive. Using revolutionary technology and underwater filming equipment, we will reveal hunting strategies and social behaviors that will change our understanding of the world's greatest predator.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E6
programme.desc: Animals come in all shapes and sizes, born with the DNA of a survivor. If you're not the predator, you're the prey. From lion cubs to Tasmanian devils, their aggression and survival instincts are prevalent upon birth, coming out of the womb swinging. They learn the stealth, speed, and power techniques to kill as they mature. But don't underestimate the young as these animals are Born To Kill.

programme.title: Wild Cats Of India E1
programme.desc: India's big cats remain the soul of the Indian terrain - acting as charismatic ambassadors for the protection of their ecosystems. In Episode 1, watch the snow leopard guard his kill from an unrelenting red fox and follow the lives of the last surviving Asiatic lions of Gir. Using the latest camera technology, the lives of these Big Cats have been brought to our very homes in Episode 1!

programme.title: Freaks & Creeps E3
programme.desc: Lucy is in South Africa to see the enigmatic Freaky Five: cape vultures, sungazer girdled lizards, golden-brown baboon tarantulas, ground pangolins, and chacma baboons. These animals are all important to South Africans and their traditions but they have been overlooked for years. Now Lucy is on a mission to reveal the mysterious lives of those lesser-known creatures.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol S5E1
programme.desc: Summer is in full swing in central Michigan and Pol Vet Services has revved up to meet the growing needs of their clients - from farm calls to clinic emergencies, Dr. Pol and crew are full speed ahead. But animals are not the only ones in need of Dr. Pol's attention, as he and Charles embark on a mission to fix up his vintage DMC DeLorean for the local car show. The car will have to wait though, as the Pol duo have the pedal to the metal en route to a serious emergency - Bow Tie, a beloved family cow has suffered an enormous prolapse after giving birth. The longer the uterus is out the more it swells, so time is of the essence if they are to save Bow Tie in this emergency farm call. While Dr. Pol and Charles have their hands full, Dr. Brenda is headed to Caryl Dairy where the situation is grim for a cow struggling to give birth. With zero progress made since Dr. Brenda's arrival, the focus shifts from delivering the calf to saving the mother. Dr. Brenda resorts to a last ditc.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E5
programme.desc: A mother's love is tested to its limits when Pula has no choice but leave her young cub alone in the Kingdom. The Matahta and Western Prides vie for supremacy, as their king finally reveals his devious plan. With the Makulu pack training its latest recruits, Kitso prepares to wage war on the hyena's reign of terror, while hyena queen Mmamotse faces revolt from within her own clan as her spoiled daughter Lasedi stirs up trouble.

programme.title: Hunt For The Giant Squid
programme.desc: Antarctica is the coldest place on Earth. It's too harsh for most life forms to survive on land. But underwater life is totally different. Using deep-sea submersibles equipped with state-of-the-art cameras, marine biologists set out to explore one of the world's most exotic places. The Southern Sea is home to bizarre and sometimes gigantic sea creatures. The scientist's journey takes us into a hostile and inaccessible world locked away under snow and ice to experience the magic spell of these ocean giants.

programme.title: World's Deadliest Compilations E2
programme.desc: The ocean is a predator's paradise. In waters bustling with life, creatures develop sophisticated skills and weaponry to survive and thrive. From coastal reef assassins to goliaths of the deep, these hunters deal out a one-way ticket to Davy Jones' locker.

programme.title: The Pack E2
programme.desc: A single African Hunting Dog is a tough, agile predator. A pack of them is a singular force of nature, able to take on prey many times their size and strength. Travel to Umfolozi Game Reserve in South Africa, and uncover how allegiances are built, strategies planned and teamwork developed, turning these canines into an elite hunting unit.

programme.title: Wild Sri Lanka E1
programme.desc: The seas surrounding Sri Lanka boasts an incredible array of habitats, all full of life. Sri Lanka's seas tell us much about how the island came to be – the vast, slow forces that underpin the extraordinary diversity of the island we see today. They also tell the story of Sri Lanka's complex climate and the ancient roots of many of the species that inhabit the island today.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E6
programme.desc: A huge black mamba hides under the kitchen sink, Simon rips apart a couch to find a spitter and climbs a tree to catch a highly-venomous vine snake.

programme.title: Hostile Planet E5
programme.desc: Delve beneath the surface of the largest habitat on Earth - our oceans - to uncover a world of extraordinary extremes from crushing depths to stormy coasts and vast blue deserts to crowded reefs. Oceans are dynamic environments where animals must adapt to life of constant change. Discover how seals fend off sharks; how turtles risk their lives to create their next generation; and how ingenious orca fight to survive in the face of ever-increasing competition.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E4
programme.desc: Ben and Francis head out to meet with Max, who is looking to create one of the largest residential tanks of its kind in Southern Florida. With the specialized filtration system, the entire aquarium runs in the ballpark of $40,000. Then, it's up to Mat and Ben to take on a new client, former Miami Heat star, Alonzo Mourning, who wants an aquarium for a youth center which helps at-risk youth.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E7
programme.desc: At every corner of the world, there is a battle for survival as aquatic and terrestrial creatures meet and engage in combat. Some prowl for unsuspecting prey, others battle their own for supremacy, and there are those hoping to live another day. From the Arctic to rocky beaches, the African savannah to the seas, these ferocious wars rage through battlefields on land and in water.

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E1
programme.desc: In the animal kingdom there are covert assassins lurking in the shadows, ready to pounce at lightning speed to fight for survival and battle their foes. Possessing the skills to kill, these world's deadliest animals will use their jaw-dropping talents to fight to live another day. From stealthy cats to patient seals, giant centipedes to kick-boxing kangaroos, these are the Animal Ninja Warriors.

programme.title: Japan's Wild Year
programme.desc: Japan is synonymous with crowded high tech cities. In fact around three-quarters of Japan is uninhabited forests, mountains and coast lines. Here a great diversity of wildlife ekes out an existence adapted to a country with great extremes of climate. From the tropics in the south to the sub-arctic climate of Hokkaido island. From the northernmost primates in the world, the snow monkeys, bears, giant hornets and the weird goat-antelope serow, to the iconic red-headed crane and the abundant cherry salmon, the life blood of Japanese rivers.

programme.title: World's Deadliest Crocs
programme.desc: Big crocs are watching us. Following our boats, learning our moves. They're smart, hungry? And massive. How big can they get? And what gives them the taste for human flesh? Who are the World's Deadliest Crocs? Through croc attack stories/re-cres we explore the latest behaviors and status of the BIG 4 croc species around the world.

programme.title: Hooked S5E5
programme.desc: In the astounding world of monster fish, these fierce fighters wield some of evolution's deadliest arsenals – they can shock, sting, stun or slice predators or prey. We'll travel around the world as anglers dare to take on these weapon-wielding beasts. Watch as fearless fishermen fight these warriors of the deep.

programme.desc: Mat is beside himself with excitement at the possibility of creating fish tanks for the home plate backstop of the new Miami Marlins baseball stadium. However, Jose can't get back on track with his production schedule and an overlooked design flaw in the Marlins reefs could botch the delivery date. Will they be able to create tanks that will safely house the fish in the Marlin ballpark?

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E3
programme.desc: Whether it's to hunt or to protect itself against predators, there are spine-chilling killing machines ready to mutate in surprising and amazing ways. From color changing to shape shifting, getting fierce, turning up the heat, fooling their prey or simply letting it fly, these animals will do anything it takes to survive on World's Deadliest: Transformers.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E5
programme.desc: Sioux comes face-to-face with a Green mamba, Simon is almost bitten by a Black mamba and they catch two bizarre snakes that don't belong in Durban!

programme.title: World's Deadliest (2019) E1
programme.desc: Carnivores are designed to kill so what happens when the deadliest go head to head? Meerkats fight in the deserts, a cuttlefish turns a reef into a warzone, a killer shrew wreaks havoc in the fields, baby alligators fight to survive the deadly swamp, Lions take on hyenas and tigers take on each other as carnivores battle each other to survive Nature's eternal war.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E1
programme.desc: On Indonesias eastern frontier lies an ancient world forged by fire. Isolated for thousands of years it is a land of extremes where creatures have evolved beyond recognition. Each habitat harbours a unique mix of the bold and the bizarre as Papuas lost worlds support one of the richest and strangest concentrations of life on our planet.

programme.title: Wild Indonesia (2015) E2
programme.desc: Borneo is the worlds third largest island, and Sumatra is no dwarf in comparison. Both islands became cut off from the Asian mainland when sea levels rose at the end of the last ice age 12,000 years ago. Large animals became marooned, isolated from their mainland cousins. Over time, they have adapted and evolved to their new home developing an array of unique traits on each island. Today, these are the Islands of Monsters.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S1E2
programme.desc: Leaving Ben in charge of the warehouse, Mat takes off to the Caribbean island of Curacao with Allan Marshall, who runs biological operations at the Florida Aquarium, to locate some deep sea fish for a new exhibit. Meanwhile, the guys in the warehouse are stretched to the limit as Mat has promised a repeat client a 3000-gallon aquarium in just three weeks!

programme.title: World's Deadliest S2E8
programme.desc: What's hungrier than a predator? The underdog that fights back. Even the king of the jungle can be a victim in the wild. Watch as aggressive cape buffaloes toss a lion like a rag doll, a gazelle gets loose from a cheetah's grip and charges at him, and a tiger shark looking for food becomes food for orcas. The only hierarchy in the animal kingdom that matters is the survival of the fittest.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E6
programme.desc: Snake catcher Simon Keys and Siouxsie Gillett's business poses life and death situations. programme.desc: Berbagai masalah dan kekacauan terjadi ketika seorang nenek berusia 70 tahun yang tidak akur dengan keluarga putranya secara ajaib kembali menjadi dirinya saat berumur 20 tahun.

programme.title: The Tooth And The Nail
programme.desc: Berdasarkan novel karya Bill S. Ballinger dengan judul yang sama, film ini menceritakan tentang seorang pesulap yang merencanakan trik paling rumit untuk mengungkap konspirasi tersembunyi di balik kematian tunangannya.

programme.title: The Fatal Encounter
programme.desc: Raja Jeongjo diancam oleh faksi Nowon dan Soron yang menjadi lawannya dan berjuang untuk melindungi takhtanya. Ia menghadapi perlawanan dari segala arah dan menjadi target pembunuhan.

programme.title: Kim Ji Young, Born 1982
programme.desc: Kim Ji-young, seorang wanita Korea berusia 30-an, tiba-tiba menunjukkan tanda-tanda dirasuki oleh sosok almarhum ibu dan kakak perempuannya setelah ia menjadi ibu rumah tangga.

programme.title: The Spies
programme.desc: Kim, seorang mata-mata Korea Utara yang telah tinggal di Korea Selatan selama 22 tahun tiba-tiba dihubungi oleh atasannya. Mereka berencana untuk menyelesaikan misi sebelumnya dan mencuri uang simpanan target sebanyak-banyaknya.

programme.title: We Are Brothers
programme.desc: Dua kakak beradik yang terpisah sejak lahir bersatu kembali 30 tahun kemudian dan melakukan perjalanan untuk mencari ibu mereka yang menderita Alzheimer.

programme.title: Gangster, The Cop, The Devil
programme.desc: Setelah nyaris tewas dari serangan seorang pembunuh berantai nan kejam, seorang bos kriminal bekerjasama dengan seorang detektif setempat untuk menangkap sang pembunuh.

programme.title: The Chronicles Of Evil
programme.desc: Seorang detektif harus mengurai kesalahan di masa lalu untuk mencari tahu mengapa ia menjadi target utama dan menjadi pembunuh seorang sopir taksi.

programme.title: RV: Resurrected Victims
programme.desc: Suatu hari, ibu jaksa Jin-hong yang sudah meninggal kembali ke rumah dan mencoba membunuhnya. Ia pun segera menjadi tersangka utama atas pembunuhan ibunya.

programme.title: Asura: The City Of Madness
programme.desc: Seorang detektif yang melakukan 'pekerjaan kotor' secara diam-diam untuk seorang walikota nan korup, terpaksa bekerja sama dengan seorang jaksa nan kejam untuk melakukan penyelidikan terhadap sang walikota.

programme.title: Hit-And-Run Squad
programme.desc: Seorang detektif polisi veteran dan seorang polisi muda bekerjasama untuk menangkap seorang pengusaha kaya raya sekaligus pembalap yang gila kecepatan dan kekuasaan.

programme.title: The Classified File
programme.desc: Seorang detektif veteran dan sesosok peramal menjalin kerja sama yang tidak biasa untuk menyelamatkan seorang anak yang diculik sebelum terlambat.

programme.title: Truck
programme.desc: Seorang sopir truk tak sengaja melihat pembunuhan oleh sebuah geng. Ia bersedia membantu membuang mayat-mayat itu agar tetap dibiarkan hidup. Namun, situasi memburuk ketika seorang pembunuh berantai menumpang truknya.

programme.title: Heung-boo: The Revolutionist
programme.desc: Sebuah sandiwara jalanan menjadi populer pada masa Dinasti Joseon. Heung-boo, sang penulis naskah, banyak diincar oleh para elit politik yang ingin menggunakan ketenarannya untuk kepentingan mereka sendiri.

programme.title: The Accidental Detective
programme.desc: Seorang penulis blog kriminal dan seorang detektif veteran bekerjasama demi membuktikan bahwa teman mereka tidak bersalah dan dijadikan kambing hitam atas pembunuhan nan keji.

programme.title: Love Guide For Dumpees
programme.desc: Dua orang yang baru saja dicampakkan menghabiskan malam dengan mabuk bersama untuk melupakan mantan mereka, lalu sepakat untuk bertemu sembilan kali lagi sebelum berjanji untuk tidak bertemu lagi.

programme.desc: Akibat kesalahan di surga, seorang pengacara nan tak percaya cinta tewas dalam kecelakaan mobil. Guna menutupi kesalahan mereka, ia harus hidup sebagai ibu rumah tangga selama sebulan demi kembali ke kehidupan lamanya.
